
INSTALLATION:

1. Get sources from SVN server

svn co https://rsf.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/rsf/trunk RSF

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Configure bash for installation

export RSFROOT=/usr/local/rsf
if [ -n "$PYTHONPATH" ]; then
export PYTHONPATH=${PYTHONPATH}:$RSFROOT/lib
else
export PYTHONPATH=$RSFROOT/lib
fi
export PATH=$PATH:$RSFROOT/bin
export DATAPATH=/var/tmp/

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. mkdir $RSFROOT (open read/write permissions to non-root users)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. Configure and install RSF

cd ~/RSF
install scons (if needed; available in ~/RSF/scons)
./configure
scons install

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NOTES

1. The tested codes are
~/RSF/user/psava/Mawefd.c (used for target da.rsf)
and
~/RSF/user/psava/Mewefd.c (used for target de.rsf)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. The output files consist of 
- a text header file (e.g. da.rsf)
- a binary data file
  - find the location of the binary by running
    sfin da.rsf

  - the binary file is the one listed as
    in="..."

    e.g. in="/scratch/cwp/emodel/bpait/da.rsf@"

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Change the number of processors used for testing by editing the SConstruct
file in ~/RSF/book/cwp/emodel/bpait and updating the parameter ompnth

e.g. 'ompnth':4 for paralel execution with 4 threads

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TEST

1. Run example

cd ~/RSF/book/cwp/emodel/bpait
scons da.rsf (to run acoustic modeling)
scons de.rsf (to run elastic modeling)

for values of ompnth=1,2,4,8,16

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

RESULTS

1. return total execution times for all values of ompnth

2. return da.rsf and the binary from in="..." for the run with ompnth=16

3. return de.rsf and the binary from in="..." for the run with ompnth=16